 the Latin motto on the French captial's coat of arms, saying: \\\"We have been working for two years on the ceremony and yesterday morning we did not know we had an extra guest, the rain, but we have this phrase in Paris, \\u200b\\u200b\\u200b\\u200b\\u200b\\u200bFluctuat Nec Mergitur (\\\"tossed [by the waves] but not sunk\\\"), and this is the spirit of Paris that got mixed with the spirit of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 2390, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1899, \"end\": 1905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.9999655872271043, \"rank\": 3.1623150767517386e-05, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}, {\"begin\": 2026, \"end\": 2031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\", \"score\": 0.9995526233030478, \"rank\": 0.0004459973437173794, \"text\": \"Latin\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latin\"}, {\"begin\": 2045, \"end\": 2051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9575982668049955, \"rank\": 0.03637401472071256, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2235, \"end\": 2240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.034260898288915e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2249, \"end\": 2270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coat_of_arms_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fluctuat Nec Mergitur\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coat_of_arms_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coat_of_arm